narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are interested in archaeology this course is a great way to get hands-on experience digging.
See evals for the lecture part of this course- they are taken concurrently.
Yes, if you like being outside and digging in the dirt or if you are interested in archaeology and getting some field experience.

It isn't actually 8-5 on Saturdays, or whatever it says on here. For our class, we spent 3 weekends of October digging in Pennsylvania. The rest of the lab portion (cleaning&analyzing the artifacts) was done mostly independently. Next year, I think they plan to work on a site in CT, so I don't know how the weekends will work. It's great class, though!

If you're a freshman, you probably want to save this for later because you'll be on the dig from Friday to Sunday every weekend in October. But for upperclassmen, I think this is one of the must-take courses at Yale--and it's not that hard to get into.
